[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordinator decomposes into ten logical stages: episode-of-care instantiation and pathway-protocol assignment, longitudinal-store and episode-state management, cross-system context aggregation, milestone-and-stuck-workflow scheduling, channel entry, input safety screening with continuous-emergency-screening, identity-and-episode-context loading, conversation handling with pathway-grounded responses, output safety screening, and escalation routing with care-team reporting. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (episode-of-care modeling with operational and clinical leadership ownership, cross-system integration breadth as architectural prerequisite, pathway-protocol library with version control and signoff, stuck-workflow detection with institutional thresholds, and records-movement orchestration with provenance preservation).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
