[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordinator.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Episode-of-care modeling with operational and clinical-leadership ownership.** Each pathway protocol is owned by the appropriate operational and clinical leadership, reviewed before adoption, reviewed annually, and version-controlled. The pathway protocols encode the milestone sequence, expected timelines, records-movement requirements, patient-facing engagement points, and escalation thresholds. The pathway-protocol-as-code discipline is the architectural primitive that makes the coordinator coordinate consistently.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system integration breadth as architectural prerequisite.** The coordinator's effectiveness scales with its integration breadth. Day-one deployments typically include FHIR-R4 integration with the institution's primary EHR plus integration with the institution's HIE, eReferral platform, and preauthorization platform. Subsequent quarters expand integration to imaging centers, labs, pharmacies, post-acute facilities, and home-health agencies as institutional priorities and vendor cooperation permit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Pathway-protocol library with version control and signoff discipline.** Every pathway has an effective date, a signing authority, an annual review schedule, and a version stamp on every coordination event. Pathway-protocol revisions go through a controlled change-management process owned by service-line leadership, operational leadership, and compliance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Stuck-workflow detection with institutional thresholds.** The thresholds for "stuck" are institutional policy, signed off by operational leadership, and audited. The LLM does not set thresholds. The detection logic is deterministic per pathway and per milestone.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Records-movement orchestration with provenance preservation.** Records-movement actions are deterministic tools, not LLM-generated. Each records-movement action is logged with destination verification, authorization verification, completion monitoring, and provenance preservation. The audit trail supports records-movement review for compliance, quality, and dispute resolution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-episode reasoning with clear scope boundaries.** Patients with multiple active episodes have those episodes orchestrated in parallel without bleed-over. The coordinator's per-episode context is partitioned; conversations explicitly identify which episode they pertain to; cross-episode reasoning is performed only when the patient explicitly raises cross-episode concerns or when a clinical situation warrants cross-episode coordination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Episode-level outcome correlation as core post-launch commitment.** Operational ownership is jointly held by clinical leadership, service-line operations, the data science team, and (for value-based-care contexts) the value-based-care contracting team.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, records-movement success rate, stuck-workflow detection rate, escalation rate, and outcome metrics vary by language, channel, pathway, age cohort, sex, episode complexity, and social-determinant flags. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, service-line operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-team integration as architectural primitive.** The care team's tooling for reviewing coordinator activities, alerts, daily worklists, weekly summaries, and individual conversations is part of production scope. The care-team feedback path for protocol revision is operationalized.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When upstream systems (EHR, HIE, eReferral platform, preauthorization platform, imaging-center APIs, lab APIs, payer APIs, post-acute integrations) are unreachable, the coordinator degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble pulling that data right now; for time-sensitive items please contact your care team at [number]." The graceful-degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
